commitResults.messageTitle: chore(coding-standard): tweak code to follow the A-CodingStandard
Add find command for keyword search
commitResults.messageBody:
Enable users to search tasks by keyword in their descriptions.
Search is case-insensitive and returns all matching tasks in a
numbered list. This improves usability and helps users locate
tasks quickly without remembering exact wording.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-10: Add GUI to the chatbot
A-Assertions: Add assertions to check for null variables
commitResults.messageBody:
Parsers relies on the assumption that input strings and extracted fields
(e.g. descriptions, keywords, and date/time values) are never null.

Leaving these assumptions implicit risks silent failures or unexpected
NullPointerExceptions if future changes pass null values.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-CodeQuality: Refactor Eltry class for maintainability
commitResults.messageBody:
The Eltry class contained a large commented-out run() loop, duplicated
switch-case logic, hardcoded strings, and restrictive find behavior.

Let's refactor by:
- Removing legacy commented code in run() loop
- Removing unused or redundant methods
- Improving find command to support partial, case-insensitive matches

This improves readability, maintainability, and user experience.
